cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV. 

The paper is about sequence labeling, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new neural network architecture, which involves training two RNNs to capture long-range dependencies between labels, suggesting that it could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates its method on various NLP tasks, including part-of-speech tagging (POS), named entity recognition (NER), and chunking, which could also place it under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
